H0.text: Who was the Liberal Prime Minister of Great Britain from 1855 to 1858. Lord John Russell

H1.text: Who was the Liberal Prime Minister of Great Britain from 1855 to 1858. William Gladstone

H2.text: Who was the Liberal Prime Minister of Great Britain from 1855 to 1858. Lord Aberdeen

H3.text: Who was the Liberal Prime Minister of Great Britain from 1855 to 1858. Palmerston

A4.text: In early 1857 Russell became a vocal critic of Palmerston's government over the Anglo-Persian War

A5.text: Palmerston was swept back into power on a tide of patriotic feeling with an increased majority
